DATA VISUALIZATION

Category wise sales

In [22]:
df1=pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(['Category'])['Sales'].sum())
ax=sns.barplot(x=df1.index,y=df1.Sales)
for bars in ax.containers:
    ax.bar_label(bars)
ax.set(title="Sales by Category")
Out[22]:
[Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Sales by Category')]

Technology was the top-performing category in terms of sales.

Conclusion:

1.Technology outperformed all other categories in terms of sales. 2.Among all segments, the customer segment is the most profitable. 3.The city of New York leads in terms of profitability. 4.The West region ranks as the most profitable, while the Central region is the least profitable. 5.There is a negative correlation between profit and discount, as well as between discount and sales. 6.Furniture ranks lowest in terms of profit among the categories. 7.Fasteners is the subcategory with the lowest sales. 8.Copiers are the most lucrative subcategory in terms of profit.
